  "Prerequisites": "A basic familiarity with video games as a player, along with an openness to exploring how artificial intelligence is shaping the games industry, is all you need to get started with this course.",
  "Learning objectives": "By the end of this course, you will be able to identify the key risks associated with AI-generated content in game development and explain how procedural generation can impact player experience. You will also apply practical strategies to evaluate and manage those risks, ensuring that AI-driven tools are used responsibly and effectively within a gaming context.",
  "lessons": [
    {
      "lesson title": "AI-Generated Game Content",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson introduces the growing use of artificial intelligence in generating game content, from procedurally created levels and environments to AI-driven characters and narratives. You will explore how these tools can enhance player experience by offering variety and replayability, whilst also examining the risks that come with relying on automated content generation. We will look at practical examples of where AI-generated content has succeeded and where it has fallen short, helping you to develop a balanced understanding of its potential and its limitations. By the end of this lesson, you will be better equipped to think critically about how AI shapes the games players interact with, and what developers need to consider when integrating these systems responsibly.",
      "status": "draft",
