          "subtitle": "Unpredictability Can Undermine Player Trust",
          "slidecontent": "• Procedurally generated levels can produce unbeatable or unplayable sections by accident\n• Players lose trust quickly when content feels broken\n• Seed-based generation makes bugs hard to reproduce and fix\n• Difficulty spikes caused by random combinations frustrate new players most\n• No human review stage means poor content can ship unnoticed"
        },
        {
          "number": 4,
          "slidetitle": "Balancing Creativity and Control",
          "subtitle": "When AI Creativity Needs Human Guardrails",
          "slidecontent": "• AI can generate thousands of assets quickly, but quantity does not guarantee quality or coherence\n• Unchecked generation risks producing offensive, repetitive, or broken content\n• Human review acts as a filter\n• Design teams set rules and boundaries that guide what the AI is allowed to create\n• Playtesting remains essential for catching problems that automated checks miss"
        },
